{"id":792721645,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"9 months, 3 weeks","timestamp":1662440311,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/792721645/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Trapping Rain Water","memory":"49.6 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int trap(int[] height) {\n        int[] left= new int[height.length];\n        int[] right= new int[height.length];\n        left[0]=height[0];\n        for(int i=1;i<height.length;i++){\n            left[i]=Math.max(height[i],left[i-1]);\n}\n      right[right.length-1]=height[height.length-1];\n        for(int i=height.length-2;i>=0;i--){\n            right[i]=Math.max(height[i],right[i+1]);\n        }\n        int sum=0;\n        for(int i=0;i<height.length;i++){\n            sum+=Math.min(left[i],right[i])-height[i];\n        }\n        return sum;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"trapping-rain-water","has_notes":false}
